{
  "name": "Simple Wallet Demo",
  "description": "Demonstrates creating wallets and checking balances",
  "version": "1.0",
  "config": {
    "baseUrl": "http://localhost:3031"
  },
  "stanzas": [
    {
      "name": "introduction",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "# Simple Wallet Demo",
            "",
            "This demo demonstrates basic wallet operations in the blockchain emulator:",
            "1. Creating wallets with initial funds",
            "2. Checking wallet balances",
            "3. Basic wallet management",
            "",
            "We'll create two wallets for Jeff and Nancy, each with different initial balances."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "jeff_wallet_setup",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Creating Jeff's Wallet",
            "",
            "First, we'll create a wallet for Jeff with an initial balance of 50 ADA (50,000,000 lovelace)."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "jeff = await createWallet('jeff', 50_000_000);",
            "console.log(`Jeff's wallet created!`);",
            "console.log(`Wallet name: ${jeff.name}`);",
            "console.log(`Initial balance: ${jeff.balance} lovelace`);"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "jeff_balance_check",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Verifying Jeff's Balance",
            "",
            "Let's verify Jeff's balance using the getBalance function."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "jeffBalance = await getBalance('jeff');",
            "jeffAda = parseInt(jeffBalance) / 1_000_000;",
            "console.log(`Jeff's current balance: ${jeffBalance} lovelace`);",
            "console.log(`That's ${jeffAda} ADA`);"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "nancy_wallet_setup",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Creating Nancy's Wallet",
            "",
            "Now we'll create a wallet for Nancy with a larger initial balance of 75 ADA."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "nancy = await createWallet('nancy', 75_000_000);",
            "console.log(`Nancy's wallet created!`);",
            "console.log(`Wallet name: ${nancy.name}`);",
            "console.log(`Initial balance: ${nancy.balance} lovelace`);"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "nancy_balance_check",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Verifying Nancy's Balance",
            "",
            "Finally, let's check Nancy's balance."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "nancyBalance = await getBalance('nancy');",
            "nancyAda = parseInt(nancyBalance) / 1_000_000;",
            "console.log(`Nancy's current balance: ${nancyBalance} lovelace`);",
            "console.log(`That's ${nancyAda} ADA`);"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "scope_verification",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Scope Persistence Test",
            "",
            "This block will test that variables from previous stanzas are still accessible.",
            "It should be classified as 'query' since it only reads data."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "// Testing scope persistence - variables from earlier blocks should be accessible",
            "console.log('\\n=== Scope Persistence Test ===');",
            "console.log('Jeff object:', jeff);",
            "console.log('Nancy object:', nancy);", 
            "console.log('Jeff ADA balance:', jeffAda);",
            "console.log('Nancy ADA balance:', nancyAda);",
            "",
            "// Verify we can call getBalance using the wallet names from scope",
            "currentJeffBalance = await getBalance(jeff.name);",
            "currentNancyBalance = await getBalance(nancy.name);",
            "console.log('Current Jeff balance:', currentJeffBalance);",
            "console.log('Current Nancy balance:', currentNancyBalance);"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "final_summary",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "content": [
            "## Summary",
            "",
            "We've successfully created two wallets and verified their balances:",
            "- Jeff's wallet with 50 ADA",
            "- Nancy's wallet with 75 ADA",
            "",
            "Both wallets are now ready for transactions and other blockchain operations."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "language": "javascript",
          "content": [
            "console.log('\\n=== Final Summary ===');",
            "console.log(`Jeff's wallet: ${jeff.name}`);",
            "console.log(`  Balance: ${jeffAda} ADA`);",
            "console.log(`Nancy's wallet: ${nancy.name}`);",
            "console.log(`  Balance: ${nancyAda} ADA`);",
            "console.log('✅ Demo completed successfully!');"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}